Module com.example.bank_teller
Package com.example.bank_teller

Class CollegeChecking

java.lang.Object
com.example.bank_teller.Account
com.example.bank_teller.Checking
com.example.bank_teller.CollegeChecking
public class CollegeChecking extends Checking
Represents a specific type of checking account: college checking account. This type of account is provided to Rutgers' students only and they must provide a valid campus code to qualify (0 for New Brunswick, 1 for Newark, and 2 for Camden). There is no fee and annual interest is 0.25%.
Author:
Nabihah, Maryam

  • Constructor Details

    • CollegeChecking

      public CollegeChecking(Profile holder, boolean closed, double balance, int campusCode)
      Creates instance of CollegeChecking account with specified parameters. Calls constructor from parent class, Checking and sets campusCode variable since that isn't part of the parent class
      Parameters:
      holder - A profile object containing first name, last name, and date of birth of account holder
      closed - A boolean that is true if account is closed and false if its open
      balance - A double that hold the account's balance
      campusCode - An int specifying the campus (New Brunswick, Newark, or Camden)
